{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:sirach.31",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 31,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 31 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:1",
      "text": "Watching for riches consumeth the flesh, and the care thereof driveth away sleep.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:2",
      "text": "Watching care will not let a man slumber, as a sore disease breaketh sleep,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:3",
      "text": "The rich hath great labour in gathering riches together; and when he resteth, he is filled with his delicates.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:4",
      "text": "The poor laboureth in his poor estate; and when he leaveth off, he is still needy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:5",
      "text": "He that loveth gold shall not be justified, and he that followeth corruption shall have enough thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:6",
      "text": "Gold hath been the ruin of many, and their destruction was present.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:7",
      "text": "It is a stumblingblock unto them that sacrifice unto it, and every fool shall be taken therewith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:8",
      "text": "Blessed is the rich that is found without blemish, and hath not gone after gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:9",
      "text": "Who is he? and we will call him blessed: for wonderful things hath he done among his people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:10",
      "text": "Who hath been tried thereby, and found perfect? then let him glory. Who might offend, and hath not offended? or done evil, and hath not done it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:11",
      "text": "His goods shall be established, and the congregation shall declare his alms.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:12",
      "text": "If thou sit at a bountiful table, be not greedy upon it, and say not, There is much meat on it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:13",
      "text": "Remember that a wicked eye is an evil thing: and what is created more wicked than an eye? therefore it weepeth upon every occasion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:14",
      "text": "Stretch not thine hand whithersoever it looketh, and thrust it not with him into the dish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:15",
      "text": "Judge not thy neighbour by thyself: and be discreet in every point.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:16",
      "text": "Eat as it becometh a man, those things which are set before thee; and devour note, lest thou be hated.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:17",
      "text": "Leave off first for manners’ sake; and be not unsatiable, lest thou offend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:18",
      "text": "When thou sittest among many, reach not thine hand out first of all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:19",
      "text": "A very little is sufficient for a man well nurtured, and he fetcheth not his wind short upon his bed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:20",
      "text": "Sound sleep cometh of moderate eating: he riseth early, and his wits are with him: but the pain of watching, and choler, and pangs of the belly, are with an unsatiable man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:21",
      "text": "And if thou hast been forced to eat, arise, go forth, vomit, and thou shalt have rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:22",
      "text": "My son, hear me, and despise me not, and at the last thou shalt find as I told thee: in all thy works be quick, so shall there no sickness come unto thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:23",
      "text": "Whoso is liberal of his meat, men shall speak well of him; and the report of his good housekeeping will be believed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:24",
      "text": "But against him that is a niggard of his meat the whole city shall murmur; and the testimonies of his niggardness shall not be doubted of.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:25",
      "text": "Shew not thy valiantness in wine; for wine hath destroyed many.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:26",
      "text": "The furnace proveth the edge by dipping: so doth wine the hearts of the proud by drunkenness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:27",
      "text": "Wine is as good as life to a man, if it be drunk moderately: what life is then to a man that is without wine? for it was made to make men glad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:28",
      "text": "Wine measurably drunk and in season bringeth gladness of the heart, and cheerfulness of the mind:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:29",
      "text": "But wine drunken with excess maketh bitterness of the mind, with brawling and quarrelling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.31.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:30",
      "text": "Drunkenness increaseth the rage of a fool till he offend: it diminisheth strength, and maketh wounds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
